  "prompt": "What does \"dying from exposure\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Dying from exposure\" refers to death caused by prolonged exposure to harsh environmental conditions, typically extreme cold or severe weather conditions. This can happen when a person is unable to find shelter or warmth, leading to hypothermia, where the body loses heat faster than it can produce it. This can cause organ failure and eventually death if not treated. It can also occur in extremely hot conditions leading to heat stroke. People most at risk include homeless individuals, hikers or travelers caught in severe weather, and those without adequate protection or shelter.",
